<RelativeLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:paddingBottom="@dimen/activity_vertical_margin"
    android:paddingLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
    android:paddingRight="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
    android:paddingTop="@dimen/activity_vertical_margin"
    app:layout_behavior="@string/appbar_scrolling_view_behavior"
    tools:context="com.example.alphonsa.cooking1.MasalaDosaActivity"
    tools:showIn="@layout/activity_masala_dosa"
    android:background="@drawable/buttonsveg">
    <ScrollView
        xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:text=" &lt;ScrollView
         xmlns:android=&quot;http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android&quot;
           android:layout_width=&quot;match_parent&quot;
           android:layout_height=&quot;match_parent&quot;>
           &lt;LinearLayout
            xmlns:tools=&quot;http://schemas.android.com/tools&quot; android:layout_width=&quot;match_parent&quot;         android:layout_height=&quot;wrap_content&quot;         android:orientation=&quot;vertical&quot;         tools:context=&quot;historical.com.example.ahmed.historicalplacesbd.Division&quot;>">

        <LinearLayout
            xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools" android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:orientation="vertical"
            tools:context="historical.com.example.ahmed.historicalplacesbd.Division"
            android:weightSum="1">
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="Masala Dosa"
                android:gravity="fill_horizontal"
                android:id="@+id/masaladosa1"
                android:textColor="#f4121213"
                android:textSize="30dp"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:layout_alignParentTop="true"
                android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
                android:layout_gravity="center_horizontal" />

            <ImageView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:id="@+id/masaladosa2"
                android:layout_below="@+id/masaladosa1"
                android:src="@drawable/masaladosa"


                />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="INGREDIENTS:\n\n
FOR THE DOSA: \n

  	Dosa batter - as needed\n
 	Oil - as needed\n\n

FOR THE MASALA: \n
	Potatoes - 3 \n
	Onion - 1\n
	Green chilies - 3 or 4 \n
	Curry Leaves - 1 strand\n
	Cilantro - handful\n
	Mustard seeds - 1/4 tsp\n
	Chana dal - 1/2 tsp\n
	Turmeric powder - 1/4 spoon\n
	Green Peas - 1/4 cup (optional) \n
	Close the other side\n\n
METHOD: \n
MAKING THE POTATO MASALA: \n
1. Boil the potatoes and mash them coarsly. \n
2. In a kadai heat little oil, temper the mustard seeds and chana Dal. \n
3. Add curry leaves, slitted green chillies and sliced onion. Saute it until the onion is transparent.Add turmeric to it.Add 1/2 a cup of water and salt to taste,let it boil. \n
4.Add the mashed potatoes and green peas to the mixture. Let it cook together for 2 mintutes, Spinkle soome chopped cilatro on top. \n\n

MAKING THE MASALA DOSA: \n
1. Pour a spoonful of batter on a hot dosa griddle. Immediately spread it using the back of the spoon using concentric circular motion. \n
2. Add few drops of oil/ghee/butter on top. \n
3. Once the first side is cooked, you can flip the dosa or let it cook as it is. \n
4. Once the dosa is completely cooked add the masala in the center as shown. \n
5. Cover the masala with the dosa as shown in the picture. \n
6. Serve with hot sambhar and chutney varieties. \n

"
                android:id="@+id/masaladosa3"
                android:layout_below="@+id/masaladosa2"
                android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
                android:layout_alignParentStart="true"
                android:textColor="#030303"
                android:textIsSelectable="false"
                />

        </LinearLayout>
    </ScrollView>


</RelativeLayout>
